name: Psychology Building / University of Florida

name: Stadswerkplaats Utrecht
directions: In an industrial area. Cross the gates and go past a couple of car shops, on your left.
comment: Workshop for wood. Open workshop Friday 13:00-17:00, Saturday 9:00-17:00. Two gender neutral stalls with "Free the Toilets!" stickers. Very queer and trans friendly. Ideal if you're looking for a space to work on projects and feel welcome as a trans or gender non-conform person.

name: Griftpark
directions: Only during the summer months! At Blauwkapelseweg 30, go into the Griftpark, walk towards the restaurant, Dixi on your left.
comment: One mobile Dixi toilet, gender neutral. Can be somewhat unhygienic during busy park days. There's also a possibilty to use the restaurant's restrooms (they are gendered and cost €0,50 per use, when you're not a customer).

name: Wilhelminapark
directions: Only during the summer months! Close to the Koningslaan, behind a hedge.

comment: Ask for the bathroom key at the circulation desk, by default we give the unisex key unless it is in use/broken. We have a trans person on staff, and other staff are trained to be not horrible. If you want a specific gendered bathroom (downstairs), just ask for the key to it.

name: Cork and Cow (wine, cheese and tapas)
directions: There are 2 single-user restrooms.  One labelled for women, one labelled for either.  The 70 year old mother of the owner doesn't want to share with men who make messes.  So, as long as she goes there, there is one women-only room.
comment: You will not be run out for going to the rest room before shopping or having a glass of wine.  But, the owner would appreciate you considering a purchase if you have used her space.

name: Starbucks
directions: Turn left when you enter and go down the hallway. Each is a single room with no stalls, the hallway is out of sight of baristas and customers.
comment: They are single gender, BUT I've seen them used as unisex bathrooms without incident. You should probably at least pretend to be a customer, but I've a rushed in and used whichever bathroom is available without purchasing anything first.
